{"TopicId":213320,"ForumId":196,"TopicTitle":"Sun does not respect terrain","CreatedByName":"regex","CreatedById":70807,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T19:03:29Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"regex","CreatedById":70807,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T19:03:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003EKSP Version - Initial release\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003EWindows 10\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E, i7-12700KF, 3070ti 8GB, 64GB RAM\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSun shows through terrain, appears to respect sphere of Kerbin rather than the terrain of Kerbin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022FZLvCyi.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/FZLvCyi.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stinkbreath","CreatedById":226783,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-27T07:06:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://ibb.co/D4kWG62\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://ibb.co/D4kWG62\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSimilar issue on Duna. Sun clipping below horizon\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KhalidE","CreatedById":227476,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-06T21:13:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/hsA8fjV\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://imgur.com/hsA8fjV\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe sunrise is visible too early when orbiting a celestial body that is eclipsing the sun. The first point of sunlight seems to draw about half a degree inside the horizon, instead of directly on the horizon.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nFor some reason, I can\u0027t insert the above image from URL, and don\u0027t know how to upload directly from my PC.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James Kerman","CreatedById":160462,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-07T05:00:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOverlapping topics have been merged.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"serow","CreatedById":19692,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-09T05:33:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003EKSP Version: \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E0.1.0.0.20892\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003EOperating System and version: \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003EWindows 10 Pro 21H2\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003ECPU: \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003EXeon E5-1620 0 @ 3.60 GHz\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E \u00A0GPU: \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003EAMD RX 6700 XT\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDescription of the bug. \u00A0\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExpected Behavior\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSun not visible through terrain\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022f